After 89 models, 356 hours of processing, 1800 likes and 13K downloads, I want to sincerely thank the 3 people in total who supported me and allowed me to credit my colab this month. You made this possible. ❤

Taxi Driver is a 1976 American neo-noir psychological drama thriller film directed by Martin Scorsese, written by Paul Schrader, and starring Robert De Niro, Jodie Foster, Cybill Shepherd, Harvey Keitel, Peter Boyle, Leonard Harris, and Albert Brooks. Set in a decaying and morally bankrupt New York City following the Vietnam War, the film follows Travis Bickle (De Niro), a veteran working as a taxi driver, and his deteriorating mental state as he works nights in the city.

This model is trained with SFW sources only. If you get NSFW content, you did it in purpose, didn't you?

Use Travis as trigger.

items.name: Cel Shaded Artist Styles [Screencap/Official/Promo Art Styles]
items.description:
Everywhere I look, I see people making screencap style checkpoints and LORAs using screencaps from actual animes. I can't help but think that's both tiresome and time-consuming, and am surprised not many people seem to realize there are numerous artists such as Hara3131 out there that draw relatively the same way. Therefore, my approach to this kind of style is to train on those artists' styles instead, afterward providing them here for people to use.

Due to this kind of style being similar universally, keep in mind with some styles there may be very little difference.

Updates to this post will be made periodically. Remember to check the About This Version details for specifics on every LORA release.

modelVersions.name: MandioArt
modelVersions.description:
Trained on the primarily Black Clover/Seven Deadly Sins-esque style of MandioArt. Artist does mostly NSFW work. Generally combines well with other LORAs.

  • If the style isn't coming through, adding "flat color, anime coloring" to the prompt potentially solves this. Naturally, screencap-style checkpoints or checkpoints capable of similar styles allow it to shine the most.

  • Maintains overall style even if not in screencap form.

Recommended Weight(s): 0.6-1

items.name: Loona from Helluva boss
items.description:
How to use

It is recommended to write the following tokens: loona, furry, sexy furry, tight black leggins, cartoon, illustration.

Copy the prompt and parameters from the preview to this model — you will not lose.

What the model is suitable for

The model is trained in screenshots from the cartoon Helluva boss. The data was not marked up at all — which gave an excellent result.

Keep in mind that you will have to refine the image through inpaint

LoRA was trained on a variety of examples, so try combinations and share your creativity in the comments.

I trained LoRA on the Flat-2D Animerge model, so it's better to work with her in pairs.

to get a realistic result with the bluer effect, you need to set as few sampling steps as possible and lift the CFG Scale.

Generation at high resolutions is possible.

Which model works best with

It is best to use the Flat-2D Animerge model, but you can combine this LoRA with other solutions focused on photorealism, model will work perfectly with them.

Links to my resources

You will find help in my telegram chat.
My Telegram channel.

items.name: LotusRocks - Nature inspired
items.description:
Warning: May not be friendly towards folks who suffer from Trypophobia

LotusRocks is a Textual Inversion trained on some volcanic sandstone rocks I photographed. It is especially good for landscapes, buildings, and other elements involving stone. It can be used as well for creating interesting textures and forms. It can bring out wonderful Roger Dean style rock structures, cathedrals, ruins, and arches. Also wonderful for aliens, strange fashion, unusual architecture, and fantastic vehicles... Or swiss cheese, I guess.

When using this embedding, please note that some models will occasionally not put in a subject and simply present the background. This can usually be avoided by changing settings or switching models.

Trained on RunDiffusion using this tutorial:

https://www.reddit.com/r/StableDiffusion/comments/zxkukk/detailed_guide_on_training_embeddings_on_a/
